RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 98. Starter Allowance Purse 23000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 28 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) (Condition Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ HERSELF raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, moved up headed into the far turn, raced in the three path from there and dueled in the lane to pull clear late. CHICK'S SHADOW raced off the pace on the inside through the opening half mile, began to move up towards the end of the backstretch, raced in the two path around the far bend and dueled in the lane, giving way, much the best of the rest. PRUDENT SONG saved ground early, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the far turn and continued to fade in the lane. SILVER GLEN raced in the three path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the four path and faded in the stretch. SHERRY ORIENTAL trailed the field on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back further while racing inside around the far turn and was not a factor.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Mr. & Mrs. Annuncio Stanchieri & FarmIII Enterprises

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 19500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OSCAR GAZE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, swung out to the five path to began a bid nearing the quarter pole, kicked clear in the final furlong and drew off to the wire. JUST MERCY raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and improved position in the lane. CHRIS'S MOTOWN GAL dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the turn and was outkicked in late stretch but kept on to the wire. LOVELY DRAMA pressed the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, dueled from the four path around the bend and faded in the stretch. ROMASHKA reared up leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and never threatened. MAGICK MINSTREL dueled on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and tired in the lane. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START. UPON REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT HORSE FOUR, ROMASHKA, HAD A FAIR BEGINNING AND NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 97. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 20500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 29 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since February 28 Allowed 4 lbs. Cla iming Price $12,500 (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DESERT RULER stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged while saving ground around the turn, dueled in upper stretch and kicked clear late. IMPERIAL KING chased the pace setter on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the three path, dueled in the lane and was outfinished in the final sixteenth of a mile. INTER MIAMI tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path, raced in tight quarters and switched out to the four path near the quarter pole and kept on in the lane. BLAKENSTEIN led the way on the inside through the early going, dueled from the two path around the bend and faded in the stretch. OLD TOWN ROAD raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and made no bid. NEWYEARSBLOCKPARTY raced off the pace on the inside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the three path and was empty in the lane. THE RIDER OF HORSE THREE, INTER MIAMI, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE FIVE, IMPERIAL KING, CITING INTERFERENCE NEAR THE QUARTER POLE. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 29. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEXTPECTATION raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the four path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear. LAST PROMISE raced in the two path early, tracked the leader off the pace up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far bend and chased the winner home in the lane. ENGLISH LAUGHTER was sent to an early lead while saving ground around the first bend, opened up on the field while the racing up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the second turn and weakened in the stretch. HONDO GUSTO raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and never threatened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 17100. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 28 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUIS TWO GUNS raced in the two path around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend, kicked clear in the stretch and held of a closer at the wire. FREELANCE raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and gained ground late. KING OF CHAOS raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn and improved position in the lane. SKIPPERINI raced in the three path early, tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and weakened in the stretch. CREATIVE CHOICE saved ground around the first bend, trailed the field up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the three path and never threatened. BLACK SEAL raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the fr turn and was eased in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Luis Two Guns
ENTRY.OWNER: Van Worp, Robert E. and Adametz, Anne Rose

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Regi stered Florida Breds Preferred).

CLAIM.OWNER: Son of A W Racing LLC

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DORSODURO chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn, swung wide into the stretch and kicked clear. VILLAGE PREACHER trailed the field on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. DUKE SKYWALKER raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and improved position in the lane. EDMUND FITZGERALD led thee way up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn and kept on in the stretch, weakening late. MAGIC BOMB raced off the pace on the outside early, navigated the bend from the two and three path and showed no kick. THE SWAYZE EXPRESS raced in the middle of the pack through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the turn in the two and three path and faded from there. UNIQUE PATH raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 96. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since January 29 All owed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIR SAFFER saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the far bend and edged clear in the lane. ANTHRACITE led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn and chased the winner home gamely in the stretch. KOBLA MAS dropped back to trail far behind the field through the opening half mile, began to improve position coming around the second turn, entered the stretch in the four path and gained ground late. SOCIALLONGDISTANCE raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the second bend from the two path and improved position mildly in the lane. KING RAMOS raced in the three path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and finished evenly. ULTIMATE IRONY raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the three path and made no bid. REMEMBER THE TUNE raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, saved ground around the far turn and was outkicked in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG ROWDY DAN raced in the middle of the pack between horses up the backstretch, came around the turn in the five path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground to get up for the win late. CAJUN CRACKER bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, recovered to chase the leader up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two path and dueled to the wire, getting caught late. CAPE COD SUMMER bumped with the horses to both sides and was squeezed back at the start, raced off the pace early, navigated the bend from the two path, launched a bid nearing the quarter, dueled to the finish and was caught late. SUPER GREMLIN stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the four path around the turn and gained ground late. MINISTER QUINN bumped with the horse to his inside at the break, recovered to lead the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way while racing in the three path around the bend and weakened late. I LIKE BOSTON raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the two path and finished evenly. SUNSPOT raced at the back of the pack through the opening stages, navigated the bend from the three path and improved position in the stretch while never threatening. SEAX raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, moved up while racing in the five and six path around the turn and flattened out in the lane. HAPPYIZE raced off the pace on the outside early, continued around the turn in the four path was outkicked from there. PERSONAL FINANCE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and faded in the lane. ANDY WALKS WITH ME raced off the pace on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the two path and made no bid. DEACON ELI reared up leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since March 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 28 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GO MIKE raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, swung out the five path to began a bid coming into the stretch and kicked clear in the final furlong. LORD DARNLEY chased the leader between horses around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the three path and kept on to the finish. ALBIE saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and improved position in the lane. HOLIDAY DANCER pressed the pace on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far turn and faded in the stretch. CARMENOOTZ raced in the four path around the first turn, led the way on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the four path around the far bend and tired in the lane.
